</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
The family 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Ctenacaridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Ctenacaridae</taxonomicName>
was created by Grandjean (1954a) in his recent monograph; at the same time the family was divided into 3 subfamilies: 
<taxonomicName pageId="8" pageNumber="9" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Ctenacarinae">Ctenacarinae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName pageId="8" pageNumber="9" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Adelphacarinae">Adelphacarinae</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName pageId="8" pageNumber="9" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Aphelacarinae">Aphelacarinae</taxonomicName>
. The last-mentioned group contains one of Berlese's species; it is dealt with below.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
[
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Aphelacaridae" genus="Aphelacarus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acarinus">Aphelacarus acarinus</taxonomicName>
]
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
